# Force LF line endings for shell scripts (required for bash on all platforms)
*.sh text eol=lf

# Append-only JSONL with globally-unique node IDs — union merge keeps both
# sides' added lines, so concurrent branches don't conflict on the journal.
# (Union resolves textual conflicts only; it does not guarantee replay order.
# After any merge/pull touching this file, reload the cognition graph — see
# audit C-3, unfixed until WP-4.)
#
# -text: store/check out the journal verbatim, no autocrlf normalization. The
# live file is CRLF (Python text-mode writes); without -text, autocrlf can
# normalize the index to LF, so a content-equal checkout rewrites bytes under
# the servers' byte-offset replay — C-3 via a "no-op". -text makes content-equal
# == byte-equal and the union driver byte-deterministic (C-3/defense).
.cognition/journal.jsonl merge=union -text
